description.narrative: In 2021, 1,004 children under-five were admitted in UNICEF supported nutrition treatment centres and 788 children (84 percent) were discharged as cured. The support given to overcome high turnover of health technicians and strengthening capacities of 147 health workers from all 11 regions on implementation of Integrated Management of Acute Malnutrition (IMAM) National Protocol improved access to quality care for malnutrition in children for 114 health catchment areas. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/01/2022
